## ERROR TIPS

### Errors when trying to get entities at specific positions
- Ensure that the entity you are trying to access exists at the specified position. For example, the error regarding the lab indicates that there was no lab found at position (6.0, 0.0). Double-check the coordinates before attempting to access an entity.

### Errors when using entities without power
- Ensure that entities requiring power, such as labs and electric machines, are connected to a power source. The lab at position (10.5, 10.5) was reported as having no power.

### Errors when using extracting but being too far
- Make sure to move to the target entity where you want to extract from before extracting items.

### Errors when placing into a tile which is occupied by another entity
- Ensure you can place an entity to a tile before attempting placing.
